## Date selection (data-driven, queried observations.db x regression_set.json)
Query: for every date, count frozen-TP pairs present, frozen-TN (same-date diff-source)
pairs present, and target-FN pairs (frozen positive, verdict=different_family, corr<0.05,
label_suspect != 1). Ranked by total (tp+tn+fn), controls always included.

Selected 11 dates (cap ~12), 66 distinct sources total, ~177 combinatorial pairs:

Controls (mandatory every iteration):
- 1990-06-01 (3 src) — precision sentinel, tn=3
- 1996-07-21 (5 src) — control, tp=2 tn=1
- 1998-10-28 (5 src) — control, tp=2 tn=3 fn=1
- 1991-02-10 (8 src) — precision sentinel, tp=1 tn=19 (heaviest TN date in the set)

Data-driven additions (ranked by total labeled pairs, TN mandatory coverage confirmed):
- 1993-06-27 (7 src) — tp=7 tn=9 fn=7 (dual-purpose, known-good from staircase calib)
- 1994-07-04 (8 src) — tp=10 tn=4 fn=7
- 1996-11-04 (7 src) — tp=17 tn=0 fn=4 (richest TP; TN covered elsewhere)
- 1990-11-08 (5 src) — tp=10 tn=1 fn=7
- 1994-04-28 (5 src) — tp=10 tn=0 fn=7
- 2001-10-30 (7 src) — tp=8 tn=3 fn=6 (spec-named calibration date)
- 1989-06-04 (6 src) — tp=9 tn=0 fn=7

Aggregate across all 11 dates: TP=76, TN=43 (mandatory pop, well-covered), target-FN=46,
total=165 pairs >= 100 required. Cost estimate ~50s/pair (observed) x ~177 pairs ~= 2.5h.

## Config change
config.yaml: flaw_fingerprint.enabled, spectral_stationarity.enabled, envelope_corr.enabled
-> true. addon_links.rule_a/b/c.enabled left false. fingerprint.triplet.enabled left false.
No merge rule armed; population is precision-safe by construction (Task 5 moved flaw merge
into rule_a, which stays off).

